I partly remember what he said ... a blister he spoke of ... or to be smelling hartshorn ... or the 

sneezing powder ... or if all fails, to try letting the blood.  FATHER JOHN. All this has nothing to do 

with the real case. It is all waste of time.  ANDREW. That is what I was thinking myself, Father. 

Sure it was I was the first to call out to you when I saw you coming down from the hillside and to 

bring you in to see what could you do. I would have more trust in your means than in any doctor's 

learning. And in case you might fail to cure him, I have a cure myself I heard from my grandmother 

... God rest her soul ... and she told me she never knew it to fail. A person to have the falling 

sickness, to cut the top of his nails and a small share of the hair of his head, and to put it down on 

the floor and to take a harry-pin and drive it down with that into the floor and to leave it there. "That 

